  "rootCause": "Astro hydration race condition — all 46 failures stem from the same issue: login form inputs not in DOM when Playwright attempts page.fill(). The server returns HTTP 200 for /login, but the Astro island shell (generic [active] [ref=e1]) renders before the form's <input name=\"email\"> elements appear in the DOM. This is a test infrastructure issue, not an application bug — the login page works correctly in real browsers. All 9 public page tests pass, confirming the server is healthy.",
  "fix": "In e2e/comprehensive.spec.ts, update the loginAs helper to wait for the form to hydrate before filling:\n\nasync function loginAs(page: Page, email: string, password: string) {\n  await page.goto(`${BASE_URL}/login`);\n  // Wait for the login form input to be attached to DOM\n  await page.waitForSelector('input[name=\"email\"]', { timeout: 5000, state: 'attached' });\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"email\"]', email);\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"password\"]', password);\n  await page.click('button[type=\"submit\"]');\n  await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n}\n\nAfter applying this fix, re-run: sw:e2e --run 0053"
}